ly unimpressed compared with the enthusiastic speaker.\n\nAttention then shifts to the small robot. Its round white head fills the view, with a black reflective faceplate and two bright blue eyes; in the reflection, the lunch table and people are faintly mirrored. The robot’s body is white with rounded shoulders, segmented arms, and a lanyard badge hanging from its neck. It is positioned close to the lunch table between diners, near a blue tumbler and a napkin with utensils. As the people continue eating around it, the robot’s head dips and turns downward, giving it a visibly dejected or left-out posture. Nearby employees in the background glance over while continuing their meals. The robot then pivots away from the table and moves off through the cafeteria on its rounded base, its arms hanging low and its badge bouncing slightly against its chest. The man in the lavender shirt turns to look after it, while the dark-haired man lowers his gaze to his sandwich. The woman with the tray remains near the table briefly, then walks past, and the men are left sitting quietly with their food and blue cups.\n\nThe setting abruptly changes to a blue product graphic. A shiny, tilted Intel badge slides into view, first showing the white “intel inside” wording on a blue surface. It resolves into a square processor-style badge on a glowing blue background. The visible text reads “intel CORE i5 inside,” with the Intel logo at the top, “CORE” in large white letters, “i5” to the right, and a small multicolored pattern in the upper-right corner of the badge. The badge appears suspended in a cool blue, softly lit space.\n\nThe product badge then appears in front of a large crowd of Intel employees standing shoulder to shoulder in a bright room. The group is diverse in age, gender presentation, skin tone, and clothing: some wear lab coats, some wear blue or purple polo shirts with Intel logos, and others wear casual office attire with ID lanyards. Faces fill the background from edge to 